---
description: nopanic repository conventions and invariants
alwaysApply: true
---

Read AGENTS.md at the repository root before making changes: it is the
source of truth for commands, invariants, style and the release process.
The compact API reference for using the library is llms.txt.

Never violate: zero runtime dependencies; identical sync/async semantics
for every policy; user exceptions re-raise unchanged (no wrappers); no
`assert` under src/; numeric parameters validated via _core.positive_number
and remote-sourced values capped; hooks/listeners never break guarded
calls; locks never held while calling user code; hot success paths stay
allocation-free. Run `ruff check .`, `mypy src` and `pytest -q` before
declaring any change done; update llms.txt, README.md and CHANGELOG.md
together with any public API change.
